$ Windows: Settings -> Update & Security -> For developers / Use developer features

*→ Windows/settings[Settings] -> → Windows/settings/Update-Security[Update & Security] / For developers* allows to
select a how apps can be installed. This selection is intended for development use only.

There are three options from which can be chosen: 
table { ll
  → Microsoft/Store apps ☰ Apps can only be installed from the → Microsoft/Store
  Sideload apps ☰ Apps can also be installed from other sources that the user trusts.
  Developer mode ☰ Any signed and truted app can be installed and advanced development features can be used.
table }

sa:
  → Windows/settings/Update-Security/For-developers[Settings -> Update & Security -> For developers]
